                            THIS PROGRAM IS FREEWARE
INTRODUCTION:
	I did this simple game 5 years ago on HP-UX. It was my first program
	on UNIX and one of first programs in C. The code is very very ugly and
	unclean....For now it works only in 256 posixcolor mode.
	I think it is quite nice and funny game...so I realized to release it.
	the goal is to get 75% of area using a small circle drawing a line...
	if you want better game get KOULES!
REQUIREMENTS:
	Linux.X windows,256 color mode..
	ps:now truecolor modes are supported.
INSTALL:
	make
	make install
	if you have directory with some nice gifs add to
	/usr/X11R6/lib/X11/app-defaults:
	Xonix*UseGIF:           yes
	Xonix*GifDir:           <some directory>
	<not tested in truecolor mode>
USAGE:
	xonix [ussual X parameters]
BUGS:
	may crash sometimes.....

